item.title: Team Canada Mustang
item.dc:creator: @dylan_0789 dylan_0789
item.description:
@dylan_0789 wrote:

[quote=“SomethingToHide, post:20, topic:331235”][quote author=MistaBigBoss link=topic=427594.msg3167541#msg3167541 date=1270150816]

It won’t look more realistic until the model improves. Why dress up a rat? It would make more sense to improve the model.

It’s definitely improved from the last, but it could use a LOT more work.

The main problem is your 3rd dimension. It’s like you’re only using front and side blueprints and not references. They might look like they match up, but it just ends up too boxy. Cars are a lot more curvy, even a Mustang.
[/quote]the model is ok, its the material he uses on it, and his lightning, i have got some crappy models 2, if I add some glossy metalic material to them and some good sunlight, they start looking realistic

No. Until something can trick people or hold their suspension of disbelief, it’s not realistic.

I can guarantee your models will not look realistic with glossy metallic highlights and sunlight.[/quote]
The model isnt that great… The material is bad, the model itself is blatent and I spent very little time on it. The material itself was made in about 3 mins for a last min render for my 3D class
